1
00:00:05,860 --> 00:00:09,280
[woman] You had an accident.
We cleaned you up.

2
00:00:09,363 --> 00:00:12,658
-Cancer, it's a godless disease, Mom.
-[patient grunts]

3
00:00:12,742 --> 00:00:14,035
It's not your fault.

4
00:00:14,118 --> 00:00:17,788
Should we give her some space?
That was really intense.

5
00:00:17,872 --> 00:00:20,207
Morgan, I know that your generation

6
00:00:20,291 --> 00:00:23,294
is terrified of anything
that doesn't make you feel good,

7
00:00:23,377 --> 00:00:26,297
but this is one
of those full-circle life moments

8
00:00:26,380 --> 00:00:28,382
that you need to be present for.

9
00:00:28,466 --> 00:00:31,969
The woman changed my diapers.
Now it's my turn to change hers.

10
00:00:32,053 --> 00:00:33,637
These are acts of love.

11
00:00:33,721 --> 00:00:36,724
It just felt like she didn't want us
all standing around

12
00:00:36,807 --> 00:00:38,350
watching her while it happ--

13
00:00:38,434 --> 00:00:40,436
-[raised voice] It was an act of love.
-Okay.

14
00:00:40,519 --> 00:00:44,315
[woman] Do any of you know
how much I'm carrying on my back

15
00:00:44,398 --> 00:00:48,194
trying to scrape together an early
birthday party for my dying mother

16
00:00:48,277 --> 00:00:50,946
while launching a mayoral campaign?

17
00:00:51,030 --> 00:00:54,033
What are you two bringing to the table?
Have you even bought her a gift yet?

18
00:00:54,116 --> 00:00:55,367
She just took a turn.

19
00:00:55,451 --> 00:00:57,036
Well, that didn't stop Natalie.

20
00:00:57,119 --> 00:00:59,747
Speaking of,
I need one of you to pop by the store.

21
00:00:59,830 --> 00:01:03,042
-I had Leanne set aside some decorations.
-Oh, Mom, Mom, I can grab them.

22
00:01:03,125 --> 00:01:06,879
Yeah, and it's looking like they are able
to push the candidates' town hall a week.

23
00:01:06,962 --> 00:01:10,508
Good news. Tell your brother and sister
about the gift you got your nonna.

24
00:01:10,591 --> 00:01:13,719
Uh, pasta bowls from the Amalfi trip
Kevin and I took last summer.

25
00:01:13,803 --> 00:01:16,305
[whispers] She's on a feeding tube.
What does she need bowls for?

26
00:01:16,388 --> 00:01:17,473
[Natalie] What did you say?

27
00:01:17,556 --> 00:01:18,557
-Mom?
-What did you say?

28
00:01:18,641 --> 00:01:20,101
-What? I didn't say…
-[woman] Mom?

29
00:01:20,184 --> 00:01:22,603
[shouting] What do you want
for your birthday from the kids?

30
00:01:22,686 --> 00:01:24,480
I don't want a birthday!

31
00:01:24,980 --> 00:01:28,651
What do you want for your birthday
from Nicholas and Morgan?

32
00:01:28,734 --> 00:01:30,361
-Who are they?
-[Nicky] Oh my God.

33
00:01:30,444 --> 00:01:31,821
That's a good question, Nonna.

34
00:01:31,904 --> 00:01:34,782
Your father gave me a necklace…

35
00:01:34,865 --> 00:01:38,828
In Acapulco that you lost
on your honeymoon.

36
00:01:38,911 --> 00:01:41,080
-We know. Get your nonna a necklace.
-[Nonna grunts]

37
00:01:41,163 --> 00:01:44,375
It was a diamond necklace!

38
00:01:44,458 --> 00:01:46,544
Nonna, I'm a public school teacher.

39
00:01:46,627 --> 00:01:48,754
Okay, Morgan,
the woman doesn't know who we are.

40
00:01:48,838 --> 00:01:50,881
I don't think she cares
if it's real diamonds.

41
00:01:50,965 --> 00:01:52,007
Yeah, I know--

42
00:01:52,091 --> 00:01:55,761
Just something cheap and nostalgic
she can cherish during her final days.

43
00:01:55,845 --> 00:01:59,473
Is that so much to ask? Nicky,
help your sister with this, for once.

44
00:01:59,557 --> 00:02:02,434
-For once?
-All right, do a good deed, for me.

45
00:02:02,518 --> 00:02:03,644
I'm stepping out.

46
00:02:03,727 --> 00:02:05,771
Okay, fine. Thank you.

47
00:02:05,855 --> 00:02:07,690
-[Morgan] Are you going?
-[Natalie] Yeah.

48
00:02:07,773 --> 00:02:11,318
[woman] Nobody expects
you to be like Natalie.

49
00:02:11,402 --> 00:02:13,112
She is an anomaly in this family.

50
00:02:13,195 --> 00:02:16,615
Confident, ambitious.
She doesn't have to work for that body.

51
00:02:16,699 --> 00:02:20,661
But could the two of you for once
set your differences aside

52
00:02:20,744 --> 00:02:23,414
and make my mother's death easy on me?

53
00:02:23,497 --> 00:02:25,708
-Stop screaming!
-All right.

54
00:02:25,791 --> 00:02:26,750
[Nonna grunts]

55
00:02:26,834 --> 00:02:28,210
[shouts] She needs a nap!

56
00:02:28,294 --> 00:02:30,880
[opening theme music playing]

57
00:02:34,758 --> 00:02:35,885
[music ends]

58
00:02:35,968 --> 00:02:41,015
Because while you might reach that island
and finally see those gardenias,

59
00:02:41,098 --> 00:02:42,808
will it have been worth it in the end…

60
00:02:42,892 --> 00:02:43,726
[coughing]

61
00:02:43,809 --> 00:02:47,813
…if their sweet smell
is corrupted by the smoke

62
00:02:47,897 --> 00:02:50,649
billowing in from the bridge
you burned to get there?

63
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:53,068
On that uplifting note, everybody,

64
00:02:53,152 --> 00:02:56,030
I would like to remind you
that this is a fire-free zone, okay?

65
00:02:56,113 --> 00:02:58,282
-[laughter]
-Okay? We have a lot of hardwood flooring.

66
00:02:58,365 --> 00:03:00,409
If you wanted to contribute
to the food drive,

67
00:03:00,492 --> 00:03:02,286
Rose would be happy to take your name.

68
00:03:02,369 --> 00:03:04,371
[techno music playing]

69
00:03:08,626 --> 00:03:10,044
[music continues]

70
00:03:13,964 --> 00:03:14,798
Hi, Helen.

71
00:03:14,882 --> 00:03:15,758
[exhales]

72
00:03:19,637 --> 00:03:22,348
[man] You organize your drawers
like a serial killer.

73
00:03:22,431 --> 00:03:24,683
Yeah, that's the intention. Hi.

74
00:03:27,978 --> 00:03:28,979
[door opens]

75
00:03:29,063 --> 00:03:30,397
-Fuck!
-[Rose] Reverend Nicholas!

76
00:03:30,481 --> 00:03:32,024
[Nicky] Yeah. Rose?

77
00:03:33,525 --> 00:03:35,861
Oh, we're just letting
ourselves in now, huh?

78
00:03:35,945 --> 00:03:38,280
We might need to chat
about boundaries a little bit, Rose.

79
00:03:38,364 --> 00:03:40,157
-The door wasn't locked.
-Well, okay.

80
00:03:40,241 --> 00:03:42,910
-Did I hear something, though?
-No, I was just on the phone.

81
00:03:42,993 --> 00:03:46,121
-Oh. The sponsorship team can do Friday.
-Uh-huh.

82
00:03:46,205 --> 00:03:47,331
Okay, great.

83
00:03:47,414 --> 00:03:50,334
Well, that could have been an email,
but thank you for letting me know,

84
00:03:50,417 --> 00:03:52,086
and I'll see you tomorrow, okay?

85
00:03:52,169 --> 00:03:53,254
-[Rose] Okay.
-[Nicky] Okay.

86
00:03:53,337 --> 00:03:54,505
[door opens]

87
00:03:54,588 --> 00:03:55,464
[Nicky] Bye-bye.

88
00:03:56,006 --> 00:03:57,633
-[door lock clicks]
-Bye.

89
00:03:58,550 --> 00:04:00,594
[Morgan] Imagine you get invited
to a game night,

90
00:04:00,678 --> 00:04:02,596
and someone hides your crutches.

91
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:04,682
They're, like, throwing stuff,
they're fighting.

92
00:04:04,765 --> 00:04:05,599
It's amazing.

93
00:04:06,225 --> 00:04:07,309
[inhales deeply]

94
00:04:07,393 --> 00:04:08,352
[exhales] Okay.

95
00:04:10,896 --> 00:04:12,439
Can you unlock the door, please?

96
00:04:15,651 --> 00:04:16,485
Oh.

97
00:04:17,569 --> 00:04:18,529
Okay.

98
00:04:20,948 --> 00:04:24,618
Uh… You always, like, pull away
from my touch.

99
00:04:25,119 --> 00:04:26,954
-I pull away from your touch?
-Yeah, you…

100
00:04:27,037 --> 00:04:28,372
-I'm at work.
-You pull away.

101
00:04:28,455 --> 00:04:31,125
I know, but, like, you know
physical intimacy is my love language.

102
00:04:31,208 --> 00:04:34,003
-I express my inside thoughts to you.
-Yeah, I know.

103
00:04:34,086 --> 00:04:35,879
I think you're seeing
your therapist too much.

104
00:04:35,963 --> 00:04:37,089
He told me you'd say that.

105
00:04:37,172 --> 00:04:39,425
Okay, I'm sorry I don't want
to have sex with you

106
00:04:39,508 --> 00:04:40,551
in a school parking lot.

107
00:04:40,634 --> 00:04:43,887
I'm not trying-- You… you do this.
You ruin these moments.

108
00:04:43,971 --> 00:04:46,390
[mocking] You, like, make it so… Whatever.

109
00:04:46,473 --> 00:04:48,934
You… wreck things.
It's whatever. It's stupid.

110
00:04:49,018 --> 00:04:50,978
-Okay, can you just unlock the door?
-Yes.

111
00:04:51,061 --> 00:04:51,979
[door unlocks]

112
00:04:52,062 --> 00:04:52,980
Thank you.

113
00:04:55,024 --> 00:04:56,942
[kids speaking indistinctly]

114
00:04:58,485 --> 00:05:00,446
What is that? What is this?

115
00:05:00,529 --> 00:05:02,281
What does it look like?

116
00:05:03,073 --> 00:05:05,492
Yeah, Morgan, I wanted to do a nice thing

117
00:05:05,576 --> 00:05:08,287
for the woman I love more
than, like, my beating heart in my chest.

118
00:05:08,370 --> 00:05:10,539
Are you proposing
by throwing a ring at my back?

119
00:05:10,622 --> 00:05:13,792
-What am I supposed to do with this?
-I don't know, that's up to you.

120
00:05:13,876 --> 00:05:14,918
It's up to you.

121
00:05:16,295 --> 00:05:17,129
Whoa.

122
00:05:18,964 --> 00:05:20,132
[man sighs]

123
00:05:21,258 --> 00:05:22,176
Okay.

124
00:05:23,635 --> 00:05:24,553
It's very nice.

125
00:05:25,137 --> 00:05:25,971
I know.

126
00:05:26,055 --> 00:05:29,350
I don't need, like,
a fucking flash mob, you know?

127
00:05:29,433 --> 00:05:33,604
But I think I at least deserve something
that resembles a proper proposal.

128
00:05:33,687 --> 00:05:36,523
-You know?
-Of course. Yeah. Heard.

129
00:05:37,608 --> 00:05:39,735
-Um, I'll see you later?
-Yeah.

130
00:05:39,818 --> 00:05:41,278
-Okay.
-All right, I love you.

131
00:05:41,362 --> 00:05:42,529
I love you too.

132
00:05:42,613 --> 00:05:43,447
Okay.

133
00:05:43,530 --> 00:05:44,365
All right.

134
00:05:45,074 --> 00:05:46,450
Bye, have fun at work.

135
00:05:46,950 --> 00:05:48,243
-Thanks, bye.
-Bye.

136
00:05:49,703 --> 00:05:51,038
[gasps]

137
00:05:51,121 --> 00:05:52,748
[whispers] Don't be so reactive.

138
00:05:52,831 --> 00:05:53,791
[school bell rings]

139
00:05:53,874 --> 00:05:55,000
[horn blaring]

140
00:05:55,084 --> 00:05:57,628
Did I tell you I'm being honored
by Out and Loud next month

141
00:05:57,711 --> 00:06:00,047
for the work that I do for them?

142
00:06:00,130 --> 00:06:03,634
Raising money for queer people
so that they can be "out and loud"?

143
00:06:03,717 --> 00:06:05,511
Mm-hmm. You've mentioned that a few times.

144
00:06:05,594 --> 00:06:07,388
And yet, I can't surprise my boyfriend

145
00:06:07,471 --> 00:06:11,725
at work because according to his church,
he can be gay but can't have a boyfriend.

146
00:06:11,809 --> 00:06:14,311
They expect me to be nonpracticing, yeah.

147
00:06:14,395 --> 00:06:18,899
I wanna practice
with my nonpracticing boyfriend,

148
00:06:18,982 --> 00:06:21,693
not be in my mid-thirties
keeping our relationship a secret

149
00:06:21,777 --> 00:06:23,237
from our friends and family.

150
00:06:23,737 --> 00:06:26,824
You had one job last summer,
and that was to fix my roof.

151
00:06:26,907 --> 00:06:27,991
Okay.

152
00:06:28,075 --> 00:06:31,245
And you got greedy, okay?
And now look at us.

153
00:06:31,328 --> 00:06:32,621
I couldn't help myself.

154
00:06:32,704 --> 00:06:34,748
[inhales] I got a thing
for The Book of Mormon.

155
00:06:34,832 --> 00:06:35,707
-Do ya?
-Yeah.

156
00:06:35,791 --> 00:06:39,044
-Well, I'm not Mormon, so…
-I know, but you kinda dress like one.

157
00:06:40,337 --> 00:06:41,797
-[Nicky] Mm-hmm.
-[boyfriend chuckles]

158
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:44,133
I told you,
as soon as my mom's campaign is done,

159
00:06:44,216 --> 00:06:46,218
I'm gonna find a new congregation.

160
00:06:46,885 --> 00:06:48,137
And we can, you know…

161
00:06:48,220 --> 00:06:49,888
-Shh.
-…practice outwardly and loudly.

162
00:06:49,972 --> 00:06:52,182
-I believe you, okay?
-For as long as we'd like.

163
00:06:52,266 --> 00:06:55,269
Okay, I'm gonna book that cruise
this year, with or without you.

164
00:06:55,352 --> 00:06:57,438
And I… I can't wait to go
on that cruise with you.

165
00:06:57,521 --> 00:06:58,355
-Yup.
-I can't…

166
00:06:58,439 --> 00:07:02,192
-I can't wait to get norovirus together.
-That's the best part!

167
00:07:03,026 --> 00:07:05,195
You didn't need to come with me.

168
00:07:05,279 --> 00:07:07,906
Yeah, well, Mom thought
you needed a babysitter at 30, so…

169
00:07:07,990 --> 00:07:10,200
Yeah, well, she thought
I needed one growing up too.

170
00:07:10,284 --> 00:07:11,702
Where were you then, Reverend?

171
00:07:11,785 --> 00:07:14,580
Probably praying for God's protection
from your bad attitude

172
00:07:14,663 --> 00:07:16,331
and all of those cigarettes.

173
00:07:16,832 --> 00:07:18,375
[Morgan] I love cigarettes.

174
00:07:21,879 --> 00:07:23,213
No, go ahead.

175
00:07:23,297 --> 00:07:24,840
-Excuse me.
-Sorry, sorry.

176
00:07:24,923 --> 00:07:25,883
[bell chimes]

177
00:07:27,009 --> 00:07:28,010
I'm gonna get a card.

178
00:07:28,093 --> 00:07:30,095
Okay, I don't think
she's gonna read a card, right?

179
00:07:31,096 --> 00:07:32,973
It's a gesture. We're getting her a gift.

180
00:07:33,056 --> 00:07:35,767
-I'm gonna get her a card.
-Get her a card. Go crazy.

181
00:07:35,851 --> 00:07:37,811
["Firework" by Katy Perry playing faintly]

182
00:07:37,895 --> 00:07:38,937
[sniffs]

183
00:07:41,356 --> 00:07:42,357
[exhales]

184
00:07:42,441 --> 00:07:44,443
♪ 'Cause there's a spark in you ♪

185
00:07:44,526 --> 00:07:51,116
♪ You just gotta ignite the light
And let it shine ♪

186
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:52,409
[jewelry jingles softly]

187
00:07:53,410 --> 00:08:00,000
♪ Just own the night
Like the 4th of July ♪

188
00:08:00,083 --> 00:08:02,669
♪ 'Cause, baby, you're a firework… ♪

189
00:08:02,753 --> 00:08:05,631
-Hey, excuse me, I'm--
-[clerk] That's display only.

190
00:08:06,465 --> 00:08:08,550
Okay, yeah, I just wanted to try it on.

191
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:10,886
It's not for sale.

192
00:08:11,428 --> 00:08:14,181
I know, you've made that really clear.

193
00:08:14,264 --> 00:08:16,475
Um… Could you grab me one from the back?

194
00:08:16,558 --> 00:08:19,478
No, because that's actually the last one.

195
00:08:20,521 --> 00:08:22,564
Okay, good, then I wanna buy that one.

196
00:08:23,607 --> 00:08:25,067
Can you fucking leave it alone?

197
00:08:26,527 --> 00:08:27,986
It's not for you, okay?

198
00:08:28,070 --> 00:08:31,156
Seriously? It's a cheap fucking necklace
in a cheap fucking store.

199
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:33,116
-[clerk] Yeah?
-Who's it for if it's not for me?

200
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,826
-Then get the fuck out of here.
-Okay.

201
00:08:34,910 --> 00:08:36,203
Whoa, Morgan.

202
00:08:36,286 --> 00:08:39,665
Can you just accept the fact that
this isn't some hot New York boutique?

203
00:08:39,748 --> 00:08:42,751
"A hot New York boutique"? What are you,
addicted to humiliating yourself?

204
00:08:42,834 --> 00:08:45,462
By the way, he wishes
this was a hot New York boutique.

205
00:08:45,963 --> 00:08:47,589
Get your wife under control, man.

206
00:08:47,673 --> 00:08:48,590
-Ew.
-She's not my wife.

207
00:08:48,674 --> 00:08:50,467
I'm the pastor
of Glenview Community Church.

208
00:08:50,551 --> 00:08:52,636
And even if she was,
we don't need to get hostile.

209
00:08:52,719 --> 00:08:54,930
-"Even if I was"?
-Oh, Morgan, please.

210
00:08:55,013 --> 00:08:57,641
-You're a very rude woman.
-You're a very rude woman.

211
00:08:57,724 --> 00:08:59,184
Morgan, wait outside.

212
00:08:59,768 --> 00:09:03,605
Thank you, I'm gonna get this card
and two of those angel figurines.

213
00:09:03,689 --> 00:09:04,815
[cell phone buzzing]

214
00:09:04,898 --> 00:09:05,816
[Nicky sighs]

215
00:09:07,693 --> 00:09:09,945
-Which, this?
-The… the blue ones.

216
00:09:10,654 --> 00:09:12,906
And if you have a gift bag
and some tissue paper--

217
00:09:12,990 --> 00:09:15,325
-Do you have any ribbon or anything to…
-[phone buzzing]

218
00:09:15,409 --> 00:09:16,785
Just gonna put it inside of this.

219
00:09:16,868 --> 00:09:19,413
Well, they're just gonna jinglejangle
around in that bag.

220
00:09:19,496 --> 00:09:20,914
Carry carefully then, man.

221
00:09:20,998 --> 00:09:21,999
-[figurines clinking]
-Oh.

222
00:09:22,082 --> 00:09:24,710
-Okay?
-Well, all right, they're gonna break.

223
00:09:24,793 --> 00:09:26,962
[Nicky] I'm just saying,
you're a slippery person--

224
00:09:27,045 --> 00:09:29,131
I'm slippery
because I'm going to a dinner?

225
00:09:29,214 --> 00:09:31,008
-I don't think so.
-[woman] She's gone.

226
00:09:31,091 --> 00:09:34,094
-[Natalie sobs]
-Body's cold. You missed her last words.

227
00:09:34,177 --> 00:09:36,430
Nicky, you weren't even here
to say a prayer.

228
00:09:36,513 --> 00:09:39,891
Some teenybopper
from the hospital had to do it.

229
00:09:39,975 --> 00:09:42,436
Read something right off of her phone.

230
00:09:42,519 --> 00:09:46,148
Kept getting interrupted by text messages.

231
00:09:47,190 --> 00:09:48,233
What were they?

232
00:09:48,317 --> 00:09:49,318
What were what?

233
00:09:49,401 --> 00:09:50,611
What were her last words?

234
00:09:50,694 --> 00:09:52,988
I don't know. I couldn't hear.
She was mumbling.

235
00:09:53,071 --> 00:09:57,075
I kept telling her to enunciate.
Something about her gloves are new.

236
00:09:57,159 --> 00:09:59,494
Poor thing,
she was so out of it by the end.

237
00:09:59,578 --> 00:10:02,664
-She was saying, "I love you."
-I do not think it was that.

238
00:10:02,748 --> 00:10:03,957
Nevertheless,

239
00:10:04,041 --> 00:10:07,461
your sister's been here since
ten this morning documenting the day.

240
00:10:07,544 --> 00:10:12,549
She thought that it was important content
for the social platforms.

241
00:10:12,633 --> 00:10:14,301
That feels exploitative.

242
00:10:14,968 --> 00:10:17,804
Nevertheless, she died
before her birthday party.

243
00:10:17,888 --> 00:10:21,808
Okay. Well, then what are
we supposed to do with this?

244
00:10:22,601 --> 00:10:23,769
What the fuck did you do?

245
00:10:23,852 --> 00:10:26,938
-[whispers] I took care of it.
-Oh, Morgan! [gasps]

246
00:10:27,022 --> 00:10:30,067
-[Morgan] I… It's not wrapped.
-[woman gasps] Oh my God.

247
00:10:30,150 --> 00:10:32,069
It's a little something from me and Nicky.

248
00:10:32,152 --> 00:10:34,529
-Oh, from the two of you.
-Yeah.

249
00:10:34,613 --> 00:10:36,823
Natalie, look at this.

250
00:10:36,907 --> 00:10:38,450
It's gorg-- It's stunning.

251
00:10:38,533 --> 00:10:39,451
-Nicholas…
-Mm-hmm.

252
00:10:39,534 --> 00:10:41,703
I think that it makes sense

253
00:10:41,787 --> 00:10:44,247
that you be the one to put it on her.

254
00:10:44,331 --> 00:10:46,583
-Put it on her?
-And maybe say a few words.

255
00:10:46,667 --> 00:10:50,671
She wants you to put the necklace
on Nonna and say a few words.

256
00:10:50,754 --> 00:10:51,588
Put the necklace on.

257
00:10:51,672 --> 00:10:54,049
-It's done. Say something.
-Okay. I don't… I don't know why.

258
00:10:54,132 --> 00:10:55,634
Morgan? All right.

259
00:10:55,717 --> 00:10:56,927
Please put the necklace on.

260
00:10:57,010 --> 00:10:58,679
Natalie, just take this from me.

261
00:10:58,762 --> 00:11:01,056
-And move.
-Nicholas, put the necklace on.

262
00:11:01,139 --> 00:11:03,058
-[Nicky] Sorry, I'm just…
-No worries.

263
00:11:03,141 --> 00:11:05,143
Morgan, help your brother.
It's your gift too.

264
00:11:05,227 --> 00:11:06,687
Yeah, Morgan, come on.

265
00:11:07,813 --> 00:11:08,855
Okay.

266
00:11:08,939 --> 00:11:10,732
-Help me.
-[Morgan clears throat] Yeah.

267
00:11:10,816 --> 00:11:11,817
Morgan, her head.

268
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:14,486
-Just lift her head.
-What else would I lift?

269
00:11:14,569 --> 00:11:16,905
-[Nicky] Just lift it… lift it up.
-I've got it. I've got it.

270
00:11:16,988 --> 00:11:18,281
-Morgan.
-I got it. I got it.

271
00:11:18,365 --> 00:11:21,284
-[Nicky] Are you lifting?
-Oh, honey, honey. Just wait.

272
00:11:22,828 --> 00:11:23,954
It's fine.

273
00:11:24,037 --> 00:11:26,123
There we go. There we go. Okay.

274
00:11:27,124 --> 00:11:29,084
-Okay.
-[Morgan] Oh my God. Okay. I feel like…

275
00:11:29,167 --> 00:11:31,294
-I need you to lift more.
-Sorry, I'm losing it.

276
00:11:31,378 --> 00:11:32,879
-Oh my God.
-[Morgan] It's really heavy.

277
00:11:32,963 --> 00:11:34,256
-Can you lift it up?
-More?

278
00:11:34,339 --> 00:11:36,299
Move forward a bit
'cause I can't get the clasp.

279
00:11:36,383 --> 00:11:38,093
[whispers] Why is it taking so long?

280
00:11:38,176 --> 00:11:40,929
-[softly] Eternal rest grant unto her…
-[woman] I can't hear you.

281
00:11:41,012 --> 00:11:43,807
[raises voice] …perpetual light
shine upon her.

282
00:11:44,766 --> 00:11:45,684
[Natalie exhales]

283
00:11:45,767 --> 00:11:47,394
[softly] May she rest in peace, amen.

284
00:11:47,477 --> 00:11:48,854
-[Natalie sniffles]
-[Nicky] Okay.

285
00:11:49,688 --> 00:11:52,190
Oh, Natalie, did you want
to get a pic for socials?

286
00:11:52,274 --> 00:11:54,234
-Oh, Morgan!
-Ha, ha.

287
00:11:54,317 --> 00:11:57,154
-Morgan, fuck. You crazy?
-Please, have some respect for the dead.

288
00:11:57,237 --> 00:11:58,905
Nicky, you really sped through that.

289
00:11:58,989 --> 00:12:01,867
-[thunder rumbling]
-[rain pattering]

290
00:12:14,671 --> 00:12:16,214
[loud pounding on the door]

291
00:12:17,799 --> 00:12:19,134
[pounding continues]

292
00:12:19,217 --> 00:12:20,051
Coming.

293
00:12:26,850 --> 00:12:30,228
-Hey.
-Hi. Uh, can I help you with something?

294
00:12:31,313 --> 00:12:32,773
I'm here for a pickup.

295
00:12:34,399 --> 00:12:36,818
I… I think you might have
the wrong address.

296
00:12:38,403 --> 00:12:39,321
No.

297
00:12:39,821 --> 00:12:42,866
You said you were at the Glenview Church?

298
00:12:43,909 --> 00:12:46,953
Uh… Yeah. Mm-hmm.

299
00:12:47,037 --> 00:12:48,789
You came with your sister,

300
00:12:48,872 --> 00:12:51,958
bought a card, two Elsa dolls from me?

301
00:12:52,042 --> 00:12:55,837
I bought two angel figurines.
They didn't look anything like Elsa.

302
00:12:55,921 --> 00:12:57,297
And a tennis necklace?

303
00:12:59,758 --> 00:13:00,675
I…

304
00:13:00,759 --> 00:13:04,888
No, I… I don't… don't…
I don't think I bought a tennis necklace.

305
00:13:04,971 --> 00:13:07,390
I know you didn't buy the necklace.

306
00:13:09,726 --> 00:13:11,228
I'm here to take it back.

307
00:13:12,479 --> 00:13:13,522
[speaks Turkish]

308
00:13:15,649 --> 00:13:17,317
I don't… I don't… I don't have it.

309
00:13:17,901 --> 00:13:18,777
[clerk scoffs]

310
00:13:21,530 --> 00:13:23,406
[suspenseful music playing]

311
00:13:23,990 --> 00:13:26,368
-Very nice house, huh?
-Mm-hmm.

312
00:13:26,451 --> 00:13:27,786
You must have a very…

313
00:13:28,703 --> 00:13:31,456
supportive congregation.

314
00:13:32,958 --> 00:13:36,044
Wouldn't want to lose their trust,
would you, Father?

315
00:13:36,127 --> 00:13:39,047
Well, I'm not Catholic,
so I… I go by "Pastor."

316
00:13:39,130 --> 00:13:43,593
I don't give a fuck what name you go by,
you dumb-looking piece of shit.

317
00:13:43,677 --> 00:13:46,137
You don't know what you've taken, okay?

318
00:13:46,638 --> 00:13:49,474
-Okay.
-You have no idea who you're dealing with.

319
00:13:50,225 --> 00:13:55,605
Return it, or I'll make sure
your God gets very upset with you, okay?

320
00:13:56,189 --> 00:13:57,899
-Okay.
-[speaks Turkish]

321
00:13:57,983 --> 00:13:59,276
-Yeah.
-Yeah?

322
00:13:59,359 --> 00:14:00,402
-Yep.
-Good.

323
00:14:02,404 --> 00:14:04,406
[footsteps fading]

324
00:14:07,492 --> 00:14:09,661
[frenetic music playing]

325
00:14:22,257 --> 00:14:24,551
[keys jangling]

326
00:14:39,065 --> 00:14:40,150
[exhales]

327
00:14:41,943 --> 00:14:42,861
[Nicky screams]

328
00:14:43,737 --> 00:14:44,779
[yells]

329
00:14:46,156 --> 00:14:47,616
[whimpering]

330
00:14:49,409 --> 00:14:50,535
[yells] Get in the--

331
00:14:50,619 --> 00:14:53,163
Get in the… fucking car!

332
00:14:53,246 --> 00:14:54,247
[exclaims]

333
00:14:55,248 --> 00:14:56,499
[engine starts]

334
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:01,922
[engine starts]

335
00:15:08,887 --> 00:15:09,930
[music ends]

336
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:14,267
No, 'cause his is Gosling with a G.
He's not related to the eight kids.

337
00:15:14,351 --> 00:15:15,936
-[Morgan yells] Fuck!
-Oh, shit.

338
00:15:16,019 --> 00:15:19,105
Honey, what is wrong?
I am asking you, what is wrong?

339
00:15:19,189 --> 00:15:22,734
I'm fine, I'm fine, I just got my finger.
I told you we should have ordered food.

340
00:15:22,817 --> 00:15:26,780
God forbid I honor my mother
by making her cutlets on the day she died.

341
00:15:26,863 --> 00:15:28,990
They're the best cutlets
I've ever had, Mrs. M.

342
00:15:29,074 --> 00:15:31,159
Where's your brother?
I told him eight o'clock.

343
00:15:31,242 --> 00:15:32,452
-I don't know.
-Uh, Mrs. M.

344
00:15:32,535 --> 00:15:35,080
-I know that today's been really hard…
-[scoffs]

345
00:15:35,163 --> 00:15:38,583
…but if it's okay with you,
I would… love to grab you privately

346
00:15:38,667 --> 00:15:39,668
at some point.

347
00:15:39,751 --> 00:15:42,462
I have something
I would really love to ask you.

348
00:15:42,545 --> 00:15:43,964
Let's play it by ear, Max.

349
00:15:44,047 --> 00:15:45,507
-Okay? Hmm?
-Okay.

350
00:15:45,590 --> 00:15:46,758
Let's play that one by ear.

351
00:15:46,841 --> 00:15:47,801
[knocking on door]

352
00:15:47,884 --> 00:15:48,718
Coming!

353
00:15:50,679 --> 00:15:51,596
Come on.

354
00:15:52,847 --> 00:15:53,682
Come on.

355
00:15:54,808 --> 00:15:56,559
Since when are we locking the door?

356
00:15:56,643 --> 00:15:59,896
Since Susan Gopnik's garage
got broken into a couple of weeks ago,

357
00:15:59,980 --> 00:16:02,065
and all of her kids' bikes got taken.

358
00:16:02,148 --> 00:16:04,609
-Where's your umbrella in this rain?
-I don't have one.

359
00:16:04,693 --> 00:16:07,988
I can't lose my son and my mother
on the same day.

360
00:16:08,071 --> 00:16:08,989
I'm sorry.

361
00:16:09,072 --> 00:16:11,825
I'm sorry, today has not brought out
the best in me.

362
00:16:11,908 --> 00:16:12,867
I could admit that.

363
00:16:12,951 --> 00:16:15,745
-How are you dealing with everything?
-I'm not good. I'm not--

364
00:16:15,829 --> 00:16:18,665
No, I just want a minute alone
with my firstborn.

365
00:16:19,165 --> 00:16:20,709
Technically, that would be Morgan.

366
00:16:20,792 --> 00:16:23,211
We do not talk about adoption
in this home.

367
00:16:23,294 --> 00:16:26,673
I birthed you emotionally,
which is just as painful.

368
00:16:26,756 --> 00:16:27,716
You're freezing.

369
00:16:27,799 --> 00:16:29,968
-Why are we standing out here?
-You tell me.

370
00:16:30,051 --> 00:16:32,053
[frenetic music playing]

371
00:16:33,013 --> 00:16:34,806
We're making Nonna's veal cutlets.

372
00:16:34,889 --> 00:16:36,474
[Morgan] They lived in Long Island.

373
00:16:36,558 --> 00:16:38,101
Morgan, can I talk to you for a second?

374
00:16:38,184 --> 00:16:39,894
No, no, there are no secrets
in this house.

375
00:16:39,978 --> 00:16:42,731
Anything you have to say,
you can say in front of me and Max.

376
00:16:42,814 --> 00:16:45,775
And half the women in this town. Ma--
Can I talk to Morgan, please?

377
00:16:45,859 --> 00:16:48,486
[shouts] It is an inclusive
neighborhood Facebook group!

378
00:16:48,570 --> 00:16:50,030
Okay. Morgan! I need five minutes.

379
00:16:50,113 --> 00:16:52,157
I can't help who signs up
or what they send.

380
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:53,867
-Okay, okay.
-It's out of my control!

381
00:16:53,950 --> 00:16:54,993
Just five minutes.

382
00:16:55,076 --> 00:16:57,996
-[woman] How would I even begin to?
-That's all I need. Morgan…

383
00:16:58,705 --> 00:17:00,248
[woman] I mean, seriously.

384
00:17:00,331 --> 00:17:03,626
[whispers] Okay, first of all,
what the fuck is wrong with you?

385
00:17:03,710 --> 00:17:04,544
Excuse me?

386
00:17:04,627 --> 00:17:07,172
I need you to get
that necklace back right now.

387
00:17:07,255 --> 00:17:08,548
What necklace?

388
00:17:08,631 --> 00:17:12,552
The necklace you stole
after I told you to just leave it alone.

389
00:17:12,635 --> 00:17:16,222
Oh… You mean the necklace that's around
our dead grandmother's neck at a morgue?

390
00:17:16,306 --> 00:17:17,891
-Oh, Morgan.
-Come on.

391
00:17:17,974 --> 00:17:20,769
You didn't seem freaked out
when you were taking credit for it

392
00:17:20,852 --> 00:17:21,853
at the hospital.

393
00:17:21,936 --> 00:17:23,813
Look out the window!

394
00:17:23,897 --> 00:17:26,191
-Do you see that truck out there?
-Yes. Yes!

395
00:17:26,274 --> 00:17:28,693
Don't look like that.
Hide yourself a little bit.

396
00:17:28,777 --> 00:17:31,946
Okay, that man out there
followed me here from my house.

397
00:17:32,030 --> 00:17:34,949
-What?
-The guy you pissed off in the store.

398
00:17:35,033 --> 00:17:37,285
He knocked on my door
and threatened my reputation

399
00:17:37,368 --> 00:17:39,287
if I didn't get that necklace back, okay?

400
00:17:39,370 --> 00:17:40,705
I… I don't know what to do.

401
00:17:40,789 --> 00:17:43,750
So you thought it'd be a good idea
to lead him here to Mom's house

402
00:17:43,833 --> 00:17:45,710
where your entire family's having dinner?

403
00:17:49,297 --> 00:17:52,217
-Well, I wasn't really thinking about--
-About the rest of your family?

404
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:54,844
-Oh, Morgan.
-Did you just eat falafel?

405
00:17:54,928 --> 00:17:56,179
You are such a bitch.

406
00:17:56,262 --> 00:17:59,057
I'm sorry that your sexy life
as an actress in Manhattan

407
00:17:59,140 --> 00:18:02,560
didn't work out the way you want,
but I am not getting my life ruined

408
00:18:02,644 --> 00:18:05,897
because you have given up on yours.

409
00:18:05,980 --> 00:18:09,651
-Fix this, Morgan.
-It was a $79 necklace.

410
00:18:09,734 --> 00:18:12,779
It felt really fucking heavy
for a $79 necklace.

411
00:18:12,862 --> 00:18:14,823
I held it in my hand,
and it felt expensive.

412
00:18:14,906 --> 00:18:16,157
I don't have time for this.

413
00:18:16,241 --> 00:18:18,576
The Quick Post guy
isn't gang-stalking you.

414
00:18:18,660 --> 00:18:21,371
-Then go outside and talk to him then.
-Seriously?

415
00:18:21,454 --> 00:18:22,539
Yes!

416
00:18:22,622 --> 00:18:24,165
[pans clattering in kitchen]

417
00:18:24,249 --> 00:18:25,834
Okay, fine. Fine!

418
00:18:25,917 --> 00:18:27,710
-I will go talk to him, fine.
-Go!

419
00:18:27,794 --> 00:18:29,712
And you know what? If he wants $79,

420
00:18:29,796 --> 00:18:31,840
I will Venmo him 79 fucking dollars.

421
00:18:31,923 --> 00:18:33,633
-Great.
-If that's what he needs.

422
00:18:36,636 --> 00:18:38,054
-[door slams]
-[exhales]

423
00:18:38,138 --> 00:18:39,264
[sniffs]

424
00:18:40,348 --> 00:18:42,350
[frenetic music playing]

425
00:18:47,313 --> 00:18:48,273
[Morgan] Hello?

426
00:18:50,150 --> 00:18:52,026
Can I help you with something?

427
00:18:53,486 --> 00:18:54,612
What the fuck?

428
00:18:54,696 --> 00:18:56,614
[muffled] You're creeping out my family.

429
00:18:56,698 --> 00:19:00,243
I don't know what you're doing here,
but this is some kind of misunderstanding.

430
00:19:01,494 --> 00:19:02,829
You deaf?

431
00:19:02,912 --> 00:19:05,748
You need to go.
I know you can hear me. Hi.

432
00:19:07,625 --> 00:19:09,169
Hey, great.

433
00:19:09,252 --> 00:19:11,254
[music fades]

434
00:19:14,883 --> 00:19:16,176
[softly mimics gunshot]

435
00:19:16,259 --> 00:19:17,677
[music resumes]

436
00:19:34,569 --> 00:19:35,570
[door slams]

437
00:19:37,906 --> 00:19:38,823
[Nicky] And?

438
00:19:39,866 --> 00:19:40,950
Um…

439
00:19:41,034 --> 00:19:42,327
And yeah. Yeah.

440
00:19:42,410 --> 00:19:46,748
So we just have to… get…
get the… get the necklace back.

441
00:19:46,831 --> 00:19:49,626
-I know. I know we do.
-But we have… But we have to.

442
00:19:49,709 --> 00:19:52,295
-[inhales deeply] We have to.
-Okay. Yeah, I know.

443
00:19:53,087 --> 00:19:55,131
That's it? That's all… that's all he said?

444
00:19:55,215 --> 00:19:56,049
[inhales deeply]

445
00:19:56,132 --> 00:19:57,550
No-- Um, no, he didn't… he didn't…

446
00:19:57,634 --> 00:19:59,928
-Morgan, spit it out.
-He didn't say much of anything.

447
00:20:00,011 --> 00:20:02,222
But you could've warned me
about the fucking gun.

448
00:20:04,265 --> 00:20:06,100
-[whispers] What gun?
-The gun! The gun!

449
00:20:06,184 --> 00:20:08,394
The fucking gun
I got pointed at my fucking face.

450
00:20:08,478 --> 00:20:11,231
-Did you--
-What gun, Morgan?

451
00:20:11,314 --> 00:20:12,982
Did you not get a gun?

452
00:20:17,320 --> 00:20:18,571
No.

453
00:20:19,656 --> 00:20:22,867
But I had a man come to my house
in the middle of the night

454
00:20:22,951 --> 00:20:24,202
and verbally threaten me.

455
00:20:24,285 --> 00:20:26,663
-Oh, really?!
-Which was also very scary.

456
00:20:26,746 --> 00:20:30,124
Did he scare you? He came to your house,
and he didn't point a gun at you?

457
00:20:30,208 --> 00:20:32,585
-That's not the same thing.
-You have to calm down.

458
00:20:32,669 --> 00:20:35,588
-That was so fucked-up!
-Shh! Shh!

459
00:20:35,672 --> 00:20:38,216
-[whispers] You'll have to calm down.
-Oh, I have to calm down?

460
00:20:38,299 --> 00:20:40,009
-You have to calm down.
-I have to calm down?

461
00:20:40,093 --> 00:20:42,428
How the fuck are we gonna get
that necklace back?

462
00:20:44,764 --> 00:20:47,517
I'm seeing Nonna tomorrow.
I'm gonna have to take it off her neck.

463
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:49,560
-I'm gonna have to take it off…
-Okay.

464
00:20:49,644 --> 00:20:51,020
…a dead woman's neck.

465
00:20:51,104 --> 00:20:52,772
-Okay?
-Yeah, right.

466
00:20:52,855 --> 00:20:54,399
-Is there any other plan?
-No. I don't--

467
00:20:54,482 --> 00:20:55,650
-Okay, so then…
-Okay.

468
00:20:55,733 --> 00:20:57,694
-[sighs]
-Anything you wanna say?

469
00:20:58,444 --> 00:20:59,988
-What?
-"Thanks, Nick"?

470
00:21:00,071 --> 00:21:02,907
-Maybe "thank you for the offer"?
-Really? That's where your head goes?

471
00:21:02,991 --> 00:21:04,492
-It is.
-Are you out of your mind?

472
00:21:04,575 --> 00:21:06,911
-Are you? Are you out of your--
-Oh shit. That's next-level.

473
00:21:06,995 --> 00:21:09,289
-[knocking on door]
-[Max] Am I interrupting something?

474
00:21:09,372 --> 00:21:11,040
-[Nicky] I don't… Yeah, I mean…
-Um…

475
00:21:11,124 --> 00:21:13,501
-No. It's… What's… What's up? What's up?
-[Max] Okay. Okay.

476
00:21:13,584 --> 00:21:17,005
Well, I was just wondering if there was
something that you wanted to say to me.

477
00:21:17,088 --> 00:21:19,924
-[Nicky exhales] I don't…
-Mmm, I don't think… No.

478
00:21:20,008 --> 00:21:22,885
-Morgan, what's happening?
-Sure there's nothing you wanna say to me?

479
00:21:22,969 --> 00:21:25,388
-Babe, I don't know what--
-Well, how about now?

480
00:21:25,471 --> 00:21:27,056
Okay, yeah. Um…

481
00:21:27,140 --> 00:21:28,683
Anything that you might wanna say to me?

482
00:21:28,766 --> 00:21:30,685
-[Morgan laughs nervously]
-Oh my fucking God.

483
00:21:30,768 --> 00:21:33,730
-Anything you might wanna say? [laughs]
-[Morgan laughs nervously] Um…

484
00:21:33,813 --> 00:21:35,148
-Morgan…
-Yeah, yes.

485
00:21:35,231 --> 00:21:37,650
-[Nicky] Oh my fucking God.
-…Janice Dardano…

486
00:21:37,734 --> 00:21:40,069
…will you make my life by saying yes?

487
00:21:40,153 --> 00:21:42,655
Um… Mom, what about… what about Nonna?

488
00:21:42,739 --> 00:21:44,240
-The timing is not, um…
-[Nicky] Okay.

489
00:21:44,324 --> 00:21:46,367
Oh no, hon, she would be relieved.

490
00:21:46,451 --> 00:21:48,619
-Nicky, get the prosecco from the garage.
-What?

491
00:21:48,703 --> 00:21:50,288
From the garage, okay.

492
00:21:50,371 --> 00:21:52,290
-[Morgan laughs nervously]
-So it's a yes?

493
00:21:52,373 --> 00:21:53,541
[Morgan whimpers]

494
00:21:54,208 --> 00:21:55,209
[Morgan and Max scream]

495
00:21:55,293 --> 00:21:57,503
[Max] Yes. Oh my God.

496
00:21:57,587 --> 00:22:00,131
-Okay.
-[Max] Oh my God, it's happening.

497
00:22:00,798 --> 00:22:02,008
[Max laughs]

498
00:22:03,009 --> 00:22:04,218
[laughs]

499
00:22:05,219 --> 00:22:07,930
-We're getting engaged!
-[Morgan laughing nervously]

500
00:22:08,014 --> 00:22:09,140
Why are you so wet?

501
00:22:09,223 --> 00:22:10,558
[bell tolling]

502
00:22:19,275 --> 00:22:20,735
[softly] Oh, forgive me.

503
00:22:21,611 --> 00:22:22,487
[clicks tongue]

504
00:22:24,530 --> 00:22:25,531
[sighs]

505
00:22:32,622 --> 00:22:33,581
[grunts]

506
00:22:33,664 --> 00:22:34,791
-[door opens]
-Yeah?

507
00:22:34,874 --> 00:22:38,002
Sorry to interrupt. Can I use
the office printer for the programs?

508
00:22:38,086 --> 00:22:39,837
-Sure.
-The basement's out of ink.

509
00:22:39,921 --> 00:22:40,755
Absolutely.

510
00:22:40,838 --> 00:22:45,468
Thank you. And do you want those programs
in black-and-white or color?

511
00:22:45,551 --> 00:22:48,721
I… I don't know, Rose. Are the programs
in black-and-white or color?

512
00:22:48,805 --> 00:22:50,556
-Color.
-Then we print in color.

513
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:51,766
Then we print in color.

514
00:22:51,849 --> 00:22:53,559
-Thank you, Rose.
-[phone buzzing]

515
00:22:53,643 --> 00:22:55,353
[funky music playing]

516
00:23:04,779 --> 00:23:06,030
[girl] Miss Morgan?

517
00:23:07,031 --> 00:23:08,574
You look like a bad witch.

518
00:23:09,659 --> 00:23:10,743
Thanks, Mackenzie.

519
00:23:10,827 --> 00:23:12,912
-[loud thud]
-[children scream]

520
00:23:12,995 --> 00:23:15,206
[music continues]

521
00:23:32,390 --> 00:23:34,267
-[woman] Nicholas.
-[Nicky screams]

522
00:23:34,350 --> 00:23:37,270
-Honey. Calm down.
-What?! [sighs]

523
00:23:37,353 --> 00:23:41,607
I just got word your nonna's best friend,
Dina, slipped at a Five Guys last night.

524
00:23:41,691 --> 00:23:42,942
-What?
-Broke her neck.

525
00:23:43,025 --> 00:23:45,319
She'll be in the hospital
for the rest of her life.

526
00:23:45,403 --> 00:23:47,280
So you're gonna have to read
her poem, okay?

527
00:23:47,363 --> 00:23:48,322
And your father's here,

528
00:23:48,406 --> 00:23:50,658
speaking of somebody
who should've slipped at a Five Guys.

529
00:23:50,741 --> 00:23:52,160
-Ma.
-What?

530
00:23:52,243 --> 00:23:54,745
If we don't have laughter
in these moments, what do we have?

531
00:23:54,829 --> 00:23:57,165
-He left Denise at home, which was decent.
-Ah.

532
00:23:57,248 --> 00:23:58,249
[Max] Okay.

533
00:23:59,083 --> 00:24:00,710
-Good to roll, Mrs. M?
-Yep.

534
00:24:00,793 --> 00:24:01,711
[Nicky] Uh…

535
00:24:01,794 --> 00:24:03,129
-[Max] Let's do it.
-Can we stop?

536
00:24:03,212 --> 00:24:04,172
Can we just, um…

537
00:24:04,714 --> 00:24:07,216
Can we stop it for a second?
Can we just stop? Can we stop?

538
00:24:07,300 --> 00:24:10,511
[yelling] Can we stop?! Just stop! Stop!

539
00:24:11,387 --> 00:24:12,430
[Nicky exclaims]

540
00:24:17,477 --> 00:24:20,771
I haven't said a prayer.
I need to say a prayer for the woman.

541
00:24:20,855 --> 00:24:21,731
Okay? Can I--

542
00:24:21,814 --> 00:24:23,691
I just need to be alone with…

543
00:24:23,774 --> 00:24:26,027
-Honey.
-With her for a moment, please.

544
00:24:26,527 --> 00:24:28,571
She's late to her own funeral.

545
00:24:28,654 --> 00:24:30,114
You can bless her later.

546
00:24:30,698 --> 00:24:31,657
Okay? Move.

547
00:24:31,741 --> 00:24:33,743
[funky music playing]

548
00:24:36,704 --> 00:24:38,664
[woman] What in the world?

549
00:24:39,582 --> 00:24:40,583
[whispers] Fuck!

550
00:24:43,628 --> 00:24:44,795
Fuck!

551
00:24:48,508 --> 00:24:50,009
[breathes deeply]

552
00:25:02,063 --> 00:25:04,690
[Nicky] Good afternoon, everyone,
and welcome.

553
00:25:05,983 --> 00:25:07,443
[fly buzzing]

554
00:25:08,069 --> 00:25:12,698
Uh… I wish we were gathering here
under happier circumstances.

555
00:25:13,533 --> 00:25:14,575
But, um…

556
00:25:15,243 --> 00:25:18,538
but it often is in these times

557
00:25:19,038 --> 00:25:21,832
that the Lord, um,

558
00:25:21,916 --> 00:25:25,836
shows us the true cap-- capacity
that we as human beings have

559
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:30,007
to… to process and to live through pain.

560
00:25:30,967 --> 00:25:33,261
-Both emotional and, um…
-Mmm.

561
00:25:34,011 --> 00:25:34,971
…and physical.

562
00:25:35,972 --> 00:25:39,684
Sometimes it's easy to forget that death…

563
00:25:39,767 --> 00:25:40,643
[fly buzzing]

564
00:25:40,726 --> 00:25:44,480
…could be just around the… co-- corner

565
00:25:45,856 --> 00:25:46,816
for any of us.

566
00:25:46,899 --> 00:25:52,196
Um… Just look at Dina Caputo,
who just last night slipped in a Five Guys

567
00:25:52,280 --> 00:25:53,739
and is now in a coma,

568
00:25:54,240 --> 00:25:56,867
no longer able to read
her poem here today.

569
00:25:59,036 --> 00:26:02,039
Thoughts and prayers
are with Dina and her family

570
00:26:02,957 --> 00:26:04,166
at this time.

571
00:26:04,750 --> 00:26:08,129
You know, Nonna was, uh, a special woman.

572
00:26:08,212 --> 00:26:11,173
I use the word "special" because
I know she pissed a lot of you off.

573
00:26:11,257 --> 00:26:12,967
[mourners laugh]

574
00:26:13,050 --> 00:26:14,302
But she never lied

575
00:26:15,428 --> 00:26:18,472
or forced any of her family members
to lie for her.

576
00:26:19,140 --> 00:26:21,559
[percussive music playing]

577
00:26:25,605 --> 00:26:27,523
How did you not get the--

578
00:26:27,607 --> 00:26:29,442
Don't you fucking dare.

579
00:26:36,282 --> 00:26:37,491
[music ends]

580
00:26:37,575 --> 00:26:41,162
I'm gonna head home and let the dogs out.
Denise is in Tampa.

581
00:26:41,746 --> 00:26:43,164
I'll see you back at the house.

582
00:26:43,664 --> 00:26:45,958
-Your grandmother was a great woman.
-Yes, she was.

583
00:26:46,042 --> 00:26:48,169
-[Natalie] Oh, yeah.
-She was so proud of your mom.

584
00:26:48,252 --> 00:26:50,630
All right, we're good, Michael.
Thank you for that. Go home.

585
00:26:50,713 --> 00:26:53,466
Let her poodles out.
Don't want them shitting on your carpet.

586
00:26:53,549 --> 00:26:57,345
Yep. All right. I'll see you in an hour.
Hey, congrats again on the ring, honey.

587
00:26:57,428 --> 00:26:58,304
Thanks, Dad.

588
00:27:01,807 --> 00:27:03,893
[woman] Did you congratulate your sister?

589
00:27:03,976 --> 00:27:07,772
On Max proposing to her
the day Nonna died? Um…

590
00:27:07,855 --> 00:27:09,231
No, not yet.

591
00:27:09,315 --> 00:27:11,984
Congrats, Morgan.
I'm… I'm just-- It's beyond words.

592
00:27:12,068 --> 00:27:14,070
-I'm thrilled.
-[woman] Max is helping me out.

593
00:27:14,153 --> 00:27:16,656
I've got him picking up Baileys
for your Aunt Joanie.

594
00:27:16,739 --> 00:27:19,367
But we really should get back
to the house. People will be arriving.

595
00:27:19,450 --> 00:27:23,120
I don't trust what those caterers
consider hot food.

596
00:27:23,204 --> 00:27:24,413
Sorry for your loss.

597
00:27:24,497 --> 00:27:27,124
[woman] Oh, thank you so much.
Have we met?

598
00:27:29,168 --> 00:27:30,336
-[gasps]
-My condolences.

599
00:27:30,419 --> 00:27:31,712
[woman] Oh.

600
00:27:31,796 --> 00:27:33,422
It's a friend of Morgan's.

601
00:27:33,506 --> 00:27:35,049
-Uh-huh. It's my friend.
-[woman] Ah.

602
00:27:35,132 --> 00:27:36,217
That tracks.

603
00:27:36,300 --> 00:27:39,845
All right. Honey, we should really go.
Kids, we'll see you back at the house.

604
00:27:39,929 --> 00:27:40,763
[Morgan] Okay.

605
00:27:40,846 --> 00:27:41,931
Okay, see you.

606
00:27:42,431 --> 00:27:43,557
[engine starts]

607
00:27:44,558 --> 00:27:46,602
-Let's take a walk.
-[Morgan] Oh…

608
00:27:46,686 --> 00:27:48,771
I have some papers to sign, so--

609
00:27:48,854 --> 00:27:49,980
-Walk.
-Oh, okay.

610
00:27:50,064 --> 00:27:51,023
[Morgan] Okay.

611
00:27:51,107 --> 00:27:53,442
-[Nicky] We don't need to push.
-[Morgan] I know how to walk.

612
00:27:53,526 --> 00:27:55,945
Come on. Okay, give me the necklace.

613
00:27:58,489 --> 00:27:59,490
Where is it?

614
00:28:00,408 --> 00:28:01,242
Huh?

615
00:28:02,284 --> 00:28:03,327
We don't have it.

616
00:28:03,411 --> 00:28:05,913
-What do you mean, you don't have it?
-I-- We don't have it.

617
00:28:06,580 --> 00:28:08,499
What the fuck you mean? Where is it?!

618
00:28:08,582 --> 00:28:11,502
I don't know how else we can say it.
We don't have it.

619
00:28:11,585 --> 00:28:14,004
What the fuck you mean you don't have it?

620
00:28:14,088 --> 00:28:15,715
-Where the fuck is it?
-I--

621
00:28:15,798 --> 00:28:18,175
-[speaks Turkish]
-Okay, okay.

622
00:28:18,259 --> 00:28:21,679
Can you calm down? Because I don't think
talking to us like this is helping.

623
00:28:21,762 --> 00:28:23,806
What are you,
some kind of crisis manager now?

624
00:28:23,889 --> 00:28:25,558
-Whose side are you on?
-Not yours.

625
00:28:25,641 --> 00:28:27,518
-[loud bang]
-What am I gonna do now?

626
00:28:27,601 --> 00:28:29,687
[tense music playing]

627
00:28:29,770 --> 00:28:30,771
[inhales sharply]

628
00:28:30,855 --> 00:28:32,356
[mumbling] Fucking fuck.

629
00:28:34,233 --> 00:28:37,319
You have no idea
what the fuck you've done. Huh?

630
00:28:42,908 --> 00:28:45,369
-Get in the fucking truck.
-[Nicky] There has to be some…

631
00:28:45,453 --> 00:28:47,788
What if I said
I wasn't comfortable doing that?

632
00:28:51,625 --> 00:28:53,502
-Get in the truck. Get in the truck.
-No. [sighs]

633
00:28:53,586 --> 00:28:57,131
-He has a gun. Get in the fucking truck.
-This is fully giving kidnap homicide.

634
00:28:57,214 --> 00:29:00,426
It's "giving"? Those are your last words?
Is it giving kidnap homicide?

635
00:29:00,509 --> 00:29:02,553
-Get in the fucking truck!
-[Morgan] Oh my God!

636
00:29:02,636 --> 00:29:03,471
[Nicky] Ow!

637
00:29:04,722 --> 00:29:06,724
[techno music playing]

638
00:30:30,349 --> 00:30:31,725
[music ends]
